Description: Body sherd (three joining fragments) of East Greek grey ware pottery closed vessel, possibly an amphora; grooved decoration consisting of large circumscribed palmette; dark grey fabric with mica and limestone inclusions; very worn dark slip on exterior. Drilled for analysis.
Curator's comments: Sherd probably belongs to the same vessel as British Museum 1924,1201.62 and 1924,1201.63.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.008)
